In [30]:
def show_acf_pacf(y, lags_number=20):
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 5))
    plt.plot(y)
    plt.show()
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 5))
    tsaplots.plot_acf(y, ax=plt.subplot(1,2,1));
    plt.subplot(1,2,1).set_xlim(0, lags_number);
    plt.subplot(1,2,1).set_ylim(-0.7, 0.7);
    tsaplots.plot_pacf(y, ax=plt.subplot(1,2,2));
    plt.subplot(1,2,2).set_xlim(0, lags_number);
    plt.subplot(1,2,2).set_ylim(-0.7, 0.7);

In [34]:
aic_results = []
bic_results = []
params_ = []
for i in itertools.product(range(3), range(3)):
    if i != (0, 0):
        _ = arima_model.ARIMA(dat.y1, order=(i[0], 0, i[1])).fit()
        params_.append(i)
        aic_results.append(_.aic)
        bic_results.append(_.bic)

plt.plot(aic_results, label='AIC')
plt.plot(bic_results, label='BIC')
plt.scatter(np.argmin(bic_results), np.min(bic_results), marker='*', s=150, color='blue')
plt.scatter(np.argmin(aic_results), np.min(aic_results), marker='*', s=150, color='blue')
plt.legend(fontsize=15)
plt.xticks(range(len(params_)), params_, fontsize=15);

AIC BIC AR(1)
